Kernel-level privilege escalation exploits vulnerabilities in the Linux kernel itself â€” meaning no matter what user you are, if the kernel is vulnerable and you trigger the exploit successfully, you can go straight to root.

Think of kernel exploits as "god mode unlocks" â€” high impact, but risky due to potential system crashes or lockups.

